<c74object name='sp.datalooper~' category='' module='SP-Tools'>
    <digest>Record, loop, and play back descriptor data
</digest>
    <description>Record, loop, and play back descriptor data.
</description>
    <discussion><h4><openfilelink filename="SP-Tools Overview.maxpat">Open the Overview Patch</openfilelink></h4>
The <o>sp.datalooper~</o> object takes incoming descriptor data (descriptors, melbands, MFCCs, or sines) and sends them into a looper with somewhat conventional looper controls. The input can be lists or <o>buffer~</o> s and the same will be output.
</discussion>

	<metadatalist>
		<metadata name='author'>Rodrigo Constanzo, Flucoma Project</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Machine Learning</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Audio Analysis</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Onset Detection</metadata>
		<metadata name='tag'>Corpus Playback</metadata>
	</metadatalist>

    <!-- INLETS -->
    <inletlist>
        <inlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor and control in
</digest>
            <description>Incoming descriptors as a list or <o>buffer~</o> as well as control input.
</description>
        </inlet>
    </inletlist>
    <!-- INLETS -->

    <!-- OUTLETS -->
    <outletlist>
        <outlet id='0' type='list'>
            <digest>Descriptor output
</digest>
            <description>Transformed descriptor output.
</description>
        </outlet>
        <outlet id='1' type='signal'>
            <digest>Loop sync output
</digest>
            <description>Current loop position.
</description>
        </outlet>
    </outletlist>
    <!-- OUTLETS -->

